{"word":"ἐκεῖσε","slug":"ἐκεῖσε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκεῖσε</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>thither, to that place</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>illuc</el>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>ἐκεῖθεν</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to the other world</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ἐκεῖ</el> I. 2.<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἐκ. τοῦ λόγου</el> <i>from that part</i> of the story, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}